Merkel Adviser Seeks Mediation Clause in Strike Law, WiWo Says

-- B y   J u l i e   C r u z
-- 
2011-08-13T12:25:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-13/merkel-adviser-seeks-mediation-clause-in-strike-law-wiwo-says.html
German collective bargaining laws
should be changed to include a mandatory mediation process to be
followed before a strike is called,  WirtschaftsWoche  reported,
citing  Wolfgang Franz , head of  Chancellor Angela Merkel ’s
council of economic advisers.  Franz made the call after an air-controllers’ strike was
halted this week, the magazine said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Julie Cruz in Frankfurt at 
